[Our thanks to Ramon for this annual report for 2012. If there are any errors, they are mine in constructing this summary from his full report. He tells me that he and his wife are on their annual vacation until the 8 May 2013, so any queries will have to await his return, as Paula is not allowing him to take his laptop with him. I am presuming that when he returns, his report will soon be up on the Azul Laboratory website.

Otherwise, the outbreaks in Laprida (5) and Olavarria (3) are now quiet, with the last outbreak noted on 15 Mar 2013. All the veterinarians in the area have been commenting on the elevated numbers of tabanid flies [large biting flies which spread anthrax] this anthrax season.

For a map of Argentina, go to: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/argentina_rel96.jpg. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1yJb.]
